    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-09-04T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-09-04T03:00:00-05:00" n="860"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d860">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/2238: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Butrick</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-04T17:00:00+09:00"
                            >September 4, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 4—6:58 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>869. Glassford will shortly resume informal conversations with Iwamura, informing
                    him that we propose to carry out compromise decision of Shanghai Defense
                    Committee at early date and requesting <pb facs="0806" n="798" xml:id="pg_798"/>
                    agreement. Minor modifications may develop from conversations which will be
                    acceptable to both sides.</p>
                <p>Hart here.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department and Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Butrick</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
